   <h1>Re: Brakes inconsistent</h1>
   <b>Michael Wagner &lt;mwagner_at_deltanet_dot_com&gt;</b><br/>
   <i>1995-08-31 04:30:40+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>
    Bleed the brakes, don't wait around to do it. Brakes
    are important...

On Wed, 30 Aug 1995, Tobin T. Copley wrote:

> On Wed, 16 Aug 1995 msudul_at_glenayre_dot_com wrote:
> 
> > My '78 (Murray) is braking rather irregularly these days. After long
> > highway sections (infrequent braking) the brake pedal sinks rather
> > close to the floor without producing much stopping power. The problem
> > is resolved after a pump or two when brake pressure is returned. I
> > thought at first that I had some air in the brake lines, so I bled them
> > without any favourable results (no significant air bubbles produced).
> > Next Bentley says that these conditions could be caused by the rear
> > shoes being out of adjustment. After adjustment everything worked great
> > for a few weeks. Now the problem is gradually returning. The lack of
> > pressure on first stomp of the brake pedal is very noticeable when
> > driving on rough roads i.e., gravel logging roads. On the rough surface
> > (very dusty too) the pedal will often bottom out without significant
> > braking effect. A couple pumps on the pedal produces the desired effect
> > (slowing down!).
> > 
> > Any ideas? Do I need to adjust the rear shoes again?
> > 
> > Thanks for any advice!
> 
> Well, this will be a typically fast 'net reply...NOT!!  Interesting 
> question, freaky problem, so I thought I'd try to get this thread rolling.
> 
> Mark, have you been losing brake fluid?  Any wetness anywhwere in the 
> braking system that might indicate a leak in the system?  Wheel 
> cylinders, master cylinders, couplings in the lines?  Check the whole 
> length of the lines, too, since you may have chucked a rock or something 
> up on the logging roads and damaged something.  
> 
> I'd be freaking if my pedal would drop to the floor every now and then!
> 
> Any other info you could add to your description?  Any other ideas out there?
> 
> Tobin
> 
> ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> Tobin T. Copley                  Currently              =============  
> (604) 689-2660                    Occupationally       /_| |__||__| :| putta
> tobin_at_freenet.vancouver.bc_dot_ca      Challenged!        O|             | putta
>                                                        '-()-------()-' 
> Circum-continental USA, Mexico, Canada 15,000 miles... '76 VW Camper! (Mango)
> 
> 
> </pre>


